elements.desc:
Element providing a list of Google Calendars for a signed in user.
Needs a google-signin element included somewhere on the same page
that handles authentication.

##### Example

    <google-calendar-list title="What I'm up to"></google-calendar-list>

properties.name: displayCalendars
properties.desc: Displays the calendar list if the user is signed in to Google.

properties.name: title
properties.desc: A title to be displayed on top of the calendar list.

elements.desc:
A badge showing the free/busy status based on the events in a given calendar.

##### Example

    <google-calendar-busy-now
        calendarId="YOUR_CAL_ID"
        apiKey="YOUR_API_KEY"
        busyLabel="Do not disturb"
        freeLabel="I'm free, talk to me!">
    </google-calendar-busy-now>

properties.name: apiKey
properties.desc: API key to use with Calendar API requests.

properties.name: busyLabel
properties.desc: Label to be displayed if the status is busy.

properties.name: calendarId
properties.desc: Event from this calendar decide whether the status is free/busy.

properties.name: displayBusy
properties.desc: Displays the busy/free status. Use it to refresh label state

properties.name: freeLabel
properties.desc: Label to be displayed if the status is free.
